3
00:00:05.088 --> 00:00:07.215  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>She's onboard one</i>
<i>of the Reptilian vessels.</i>

4
00:00:07.298 --> 00:00:08.466  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( screaming )

5
00:00:08.550 --> 00:00:10.135  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The third launch code.

6
00:00:10.218 --> 00:00:12.095  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We have complete access.

7
00:00:14.597 --> 00:00:15.807  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groans )

8
00:00:19.686 --> 00:00:22.605  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The guardians will not let us fail.

9
00:00:22.689 --> 00:00:24.607  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The power readings from
the weapon are increasing.

10
00:00:24.691 --> 00:00:25.984  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're preparing to launch.

11
00:00:26.067 --> 00:00:29.404  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Open a vortex. Set a course for Earth.

12
00:00:31.281 --> 00:00:33.867  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The Captain wants
to take a team aboard to destroy it.

13
00:00:33.950 --> 00:00:35.493  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I need three volunteers.

14
00:00:35.577 --> 00:00:37.370  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's undergone a severe neural trauma.

15
00:00:37.454 --> 00:00:39.622  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
She's been inside the weapon.
I have to know what she saw.

16
00:00:39.706 --> 00:00:41.750  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Have her taken aboard
Degra's ship right away.

17
00:00:43.418 --> 00:00:44.919  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
MAN: <i>The Aquatics joined us</i>

18
00:00:45.003 --> 00:00:48.173  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
only because you promised
to neutralize the spheres.

19
00:00:48.256 --> 00:00:51.009  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We have a plan to disable Sphere 41.

20
00:00:51.092 --> 00:00:53.553  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If we're right,
it should disrupt the entire network.

21
00:00:53.636 --> 00:00:59.017  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Reptilians will preside
over a stronger, unified Xindi empire

22
00:00:59.100 --> 00:01:02.145  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
if humankind is eradicated.

23
00:01:09.069 --> 00:01:14.032  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If they had made us
the dominant species before the wars,

24
00:01:14.115 --> 00:01:16.326  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
our homeworld would still exist.

25
00:01:16.409 --> 00:01:19.245  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And our avian brothers
would still fill the skies.

26
00:01:19.746 --> 00:01:25.251  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We should be grateful that the guardians
have finally come to their senses.

27
00:01:25.335 --> 00:01:27.337  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Once Earth is destroyed,

28
00:01:27.420 --> 00:01:30.673  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the reptilians
will take their rightful place

29
00:01:30.757 --> 00:01:34.302  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
at the head of a new Xindi empire.

30
00:01:34.385 --> 00:01:36.471  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( mice squeaking )

31
00:01:43.394 --> 00:01:47.398  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
♪ It's been a long road ♪

32
00:01:47.857 --> 00:01:50.819  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
♪ Getting from there to here ♪

33
00:01:51.027 --> 00:01:54.614  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
♪ It's been a long time ♪

34
00:01:54.864 --> 00:01:58.451  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
♪ But my time is finally near ♪

35
00:01:59.077 --> 00:02:02.914  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
♪ And I will see my dream
come alive at last ♪

36
00:02:03.289 --> 00:02:06.292  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
♪ I will touch the sky ♪

37
00:02:06.709 --> 00:02:10.171  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
♪ And they're not gonna
hold me down no more ♪

38
00:02:10.588 --> 00:02:13.383  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
♪ No, they're not gonna
change my mind ♪

39
00:02:13.591 --> 00:02:15.969  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
♪ 'Cause I've got faith ♪

40
00:02:16.177 --> 00:02:18.054  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
♪ Of the heart ♪

41
00:02:18.763 --> 00:02:21.266  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
♪ I'm going where my heart
will take me ♪

42
00:02:21.432 --> 00:02:25.895  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
♪ I've got faith to believe ♪

43
00:02:26.479 --> 00:02:28.940  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
♪ I can do anything ♪

44
00:02:29.190 --> 00:02:33.611  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
♪ I've got strength
of the soul ♪

45
00:02:33.987 --> 00:02:36.698  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
♪ And no one's gonna bend
or break me ♪

46
00:02:36.823 --> 00:02:41.119  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
♪ I can reach any star ♪

47
00:02:42.704 --> 00:02:44.539  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
♪ I've got faith ♪

48
00:02:44.622 --> 00:02:46.457  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
♪ I've got, I've got, I've got ♪

49
00:02:46.541 --> 00:02:50.253  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
♪ I've got faith ♪

50
00:02:50.336 --> 00:02:54.299  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
♪ Faith of the heart ♪

51
00:03:04.767 --> 00:03:08.354  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They're nearly three hours ahead of us,
but this vessel is faster.

52
00:03:08.438 --> 00:03:09.772  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're closing the gap.

53
00:03:09.856 --> 00:03:11.858  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It may be faster, but it's not well-armed.

54
00:03:11.941 --> 00:03:13.693  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How many ships are escorting the weapon?

55
00:03:13.776 --> 00:03:16.029  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I can't tell.

56
00:03:16.112 --> 00:03:18.406  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
The only way we're going to be
able to destroy this thing

57
00:03:18.489 --> 00:03:19.991  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
is from inside.

58
00:03:24.370 --> 00:03:26.581  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Any luck?

59
00:03:26.664 --> 00:03:29.667  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
All of Degra's schematics are encrypted.

60
00:03:29.751 --> 00:03:31.794  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're gonna need Hoshi to help us.

61
00:03:31.878 --> 00:03:33.338  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's in no condition to come up here.

62
00:03:33.421 --> 00:03:34.839  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I wish I had a choice, Malcolm.

63
00:03:34.923 --> 00:03:36.341  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sir, she's barely conscious.

64
00:03:40.345 --> 00:03:42.597  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Can you transfer that to a PADD?

65
00:03:42.680 --> 00:03:44.057  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Something portable?

66
00:03:46.476 --> 00:03:49.854  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The favorable timelines
continue to diminish.

67
00:03:49.938 --> 00:03:52.899  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They should be increasing.

68
00:03:52.982 --> 00:03:55.985  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The weapon has almost reached its target.

69
00:03:56.069 --> 00:03:59.364  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But the Earth ship is on course
for our primary sphere.

70
00:03:59.447 --> 00:04:02.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Accelerate the transformation
around that sphere.

71
00:04:02.283 --> 00:04:04.369  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They mustn't be allowed to intervene.

72
00:04:08.831 --> 00:04:10.166  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Report.

73
00:04:10.250 --> 00:04:11.918  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We've realigned the main power grid.

74
00:04:12.001 --> 00:04:15.463  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
It should increase the deflector
pulse threefold, maybe four.

75
00:04:15.546 --> 00:04:19.467  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
But it's gonna fry just about
every system onboard.

76
00:04:19.550 --> 00:04:22.262  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Be prepared to initiate
the pulse within two hours.

77
00:04:22.345 --> 00:04:24.722  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I don't think you heard what I just said.

78
00:04:24.806 --> 00:04:27.642  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
We try this, and the ship's
gonna come apart at the seams.

79
00:04:30.103 --> 00:04:32.689  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Two hours, Mr. Tucker.

80
00:04:32.772 --> 00:04:36.359  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
The Captain told the Xindi
we'd try to knock these things out.

81
00:04:36.442 --> 00:04:38.778  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
He didn't say anything about
demolishing <i>Enterprise </i>in the process.

82
00:04:38.861 --> 00:04:40.238  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Has it occurred to you
what's going to happen

83
00:04:40.321 --> 00:04:43.241  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
if Captain Archer fails,
if Earth is destroyed?

84
00:04:43.324 --> 00:04:45.410  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Every day.
-Good.

85
00:04:45.493 --> 00:04:48.705  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Then you've already come to the conclusion
that without humanity,

86
00:04:48.788 --> 00:04:51.457  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
there's no one to combat
these sphere builders.

87
00:04:51.541 --> 00:04:53.543  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Their expanse will continue to grow,

88
00:04:53.626 --> 00:04:58.464  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
encompassing one system after another,
including Vulcan.

89
00:04:58.548 --> 00:05:01.342  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Your world is no longer
the only one in jeopardy.

90
00:05:03.303 --> 00:05:04.554  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Two hours.

91
00:05:08.933 --> 00:05:10.768  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

92
00:05:10.852 --> 00:05:13.187  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( computer beeping )

93
00:05:13.271 --> 00:05:14.605  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I think we've got a problem.

94
00:05:14.689 --> 00:05:15.773  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What is it?

95
00:05:15.857 --> 00:05:18.109  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sphere 41.

96
00:05:18.192 --> 00:05:19.736  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you certain these are the coordinates?

97
00:05:19.819 --> 00:05:21.237  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yep.

98
00:05:21.321 --> 00:05:24.574  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There shouldn't be anything on sensors,
not with the cloaking barrier.

99
00:05:24.657 --> 00:05:26.909  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But there it is and it's getting bigger.

100
00:05:26.993 --> 00:05:28.911  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Have you analyzed it?

101
00:05:28.995 --> 00:05:30.371  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Could be spatial anomalies,

102
00:05:30.455 --> 00:05:33.207  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but they're clustered much tighter
than we've ever seen them.

103
00:05:35.835 --> 00:05:38.212  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
PHLOX: They're transforming the space
surrounding that sphere,

104
00:05:38.296 --> 00:05:39.672  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
not unlike the disturbance

105
00:05:39.756 --> 00:05:41.340  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
where we found
the trans-dimensional being.

106
00:05:41.424 --> 00:05:43.009  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
They're obviously expecting us.

107
00:05:43.092 --> 00:05:44.719  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
If we're going to disable the network,

108
00:05:44.802 --> 00:05:46.846  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
we'll need to get within
a kilometer of the surface.

109
00:05:46.929 --> 00:05:48.264  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
If the ship were to enter
that disturbance,

110
00:05:48.347 --> 00:05:51.559  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
the entire crew would be dead
within minutes.

111
00:05:51.642 --> 00:05:55.188  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I could synthesize a neuroleptic compound

112
00:05:55.271 --> 00:05:58.357  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
that would keep us conscious
for approximately 12 minutes.

113
00:05:58.441 --> 00:06:02.528  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I'm afraid there's nothing I can do
to prevent epidermal decay.

114
00:06:02.612 --> 00:06:05.281  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Twelve minutes won't be enough.

115
00:06:05.364 --> 00:06:07.366  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Perhaps I can extend it, but not by much.

116
00:06:07.450 --> 00:06:09.535  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I encourage you and Mr. Tucker
to consider alternatives.

117
00:06:09.619 --> 00:06:13.331  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
There must be something
you can do to abbreviate your plan.

118
00:06:19.378 --> 00:06:20.755  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Any luck?

119
00:06:22.757 --> 00:06:24.092  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ensign?

120
00:06:28.096 --> 00:06:30.181  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not feeling very well.

121
00:06:31.265 --> 00:06:34.227  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Do you think you can get Phlox
to come down here?

122
00:06:35.937 --> 00:06:38.272  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're on Degra's ship, Hoshi.

123
00:06:38.356 --> 00:06:39.690  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Phlox isn't here.

124
00:06:39.774 --> 00:06:42.151  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm not sure what
I'm supposed to be doing.

125
00:06:45.196 --> 00:06:47.740  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The schematics for the weapon.

126
00:06:47.824 --> 00:06:49.951  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Degra encrypted them before he was killed.

127
00:06:50.034 --> 00:06:52.036  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You've been trying to decipher them.

128
00:06:52.120 --> 00:06:55.039  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I gave them the third code.

129
00:06:55.123 --> 00:06:57.208  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They wouldn't have
been able to arm the weapon

130
00:06:57.291 --> 00:06:59.043  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
if I hadn't given them the third code.

131
00:06:59.127 --> 00:07:01.212  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You were drugged, Hoshi.
You had no choice.

132
00:07:01.295 --> 00:07:03.673  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I did. I should have fought harder.

133
00:07:07.510 --> 00:07:11.180  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You need to finish what you're doing.

134
00:07:11.264 --> 00:07:12.765  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're almost there.

135
00:07:16.060 --> 00:07:20.022  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We're gonna board the weapon,
try to overload the power systems.

136
00:07:20.106 --> 00:07:23.025  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But we can't do that
until we can read these schematics.

137
00:07:23.109 --> 00:07:24.986  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I tried to jump but I wasn't fast enough.

138
00:07:25.069 --> 00:07:26.737  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You need to finish this.

139
00:07:26.821 --> 00:07:29.490  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You got the three codes,
so why don't you just kill me?

140
00:07:29.574 --> 00:07:31.492  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Didn't you say you were gonna kill me?

141
00:07:31.576 --> 00:07:35.830  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You got to pull yourself together
just for a little while longer.

142
00:07:42.128 --> 00:07:45.089  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You need to complete the decryption.

143
00:07:47.758 --> 00:07:50.678  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Everything hinges on it.

144
00:07:50.761 --> 00:07:52.013  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do you understand?

145
00:07:55.099 --> 00:07:56.517  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I understand.

146
00:08:03.065 --> 00:08:06.068  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
When we exit the vortex,
how close will we be?

147
00:08:06.152 --> 00:08:08.237  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Approximately two million kilometers
from Earth.

148
00:08:08.321 --> 00:08:09.405  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Two million?

149
00:08:09.489 --> 00:08:10.990  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If we had all five codes,

150
00:08:11.073 --> 00:08:12.950  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
we could begin that
firing sequence immediately.

151
00:08:13.034 --> 00:08:15.786  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But with three,
we'll need additional time.

152
00:08:15.870 --> 00:08:17.330  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We'd be vulnerable if we dropped

153
00:08:17.413 --> 00:08:19.540  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
into normal space
any closer to the target.

154
00:08:19.624 --> 00:08:23.753  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Do whatever it takes
to fire the weapon as quickly as possible.

155
00:08:30.801 --> 00:08:32.345  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You wanted to see me, sir?

156
00:08:32.428 --> 00:08:34.013  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I think I found a way to boost
the deflector pulse

157
00:08:34.096 --> 00:08:36.015  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
without tearing the ship apart.

158
00:08:36.098 --> 00:08:39.685  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But it's gonna mean transferring
all impulse power to the array.

159
00:08:39.769 --> 00:08:40.770  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
When?

160
00:08:40.853 --> 00:08:42.146  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
As soon as we reach the sphere.

161
00:08:42.230 --> 00:08:43.147  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sir.

162
00:08:43.231 --> 00:08:44.732  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sorry, Travis.

163
00:08:44.815 --> 00:08:47.276  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're gonna have to get us
to the manifold on thrusters only.

164
00:08:47.360 --> 00:08:50.530  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That's tying my hands, Commander,
especially with a ticking clock.

165
00:08:50.613 --> 00:08:52.782  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You can do it.

166
00:08:52.865 --> 00:08:54.700  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Look over these schematics.

167
00:08:54.784 --> 00:08:57.286  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Familiarize yourself with
the surface features of the sphere.

168
00:08:58.329 --> 00:09:01.582  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We won't be out to transport directly
onto the control platform.

169
00:09:01.666 --> 00:09:03.793  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's too heavily shielded.

170
00:09:03.876 --> 00:09:07.672  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We'll have to beam in and out
no deeper than this peripheral framework.

171
00:09:07.755 --> 00:09:09.257  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What if you need to board the weapon

172
00:09:09.340 --> 00:09:12.552  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
before your crewman
completes her decryptions?

173
00:09:14.804 --> 00:09:16.806  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm taking her with me.

174
00:09:16.889 --> 00:09:20.393  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Sir, she's hardly in any shape--
-She's been there, Malcolm.

175
00:09:20.476 --> 00:09:22.478  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That's where she deciphered
the third launch code.

176
00:09:22.562 --> 00:09:23.980  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She was drugged.

177
00:09:24.063 --> 00:09:25.731  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There's no reason to believe that
she'll remember anything--

178
00:09:25.815 --> 00:09:27.358  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
ARCHER: She's coming with me.

179
00:09:28.484 --> 00:09:31.445  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I want you and your team
to beam in right before we do.

180
00:09:31.529 --> 00:09:35.241  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Secure the closest route to the platform.

181
00:09:35.324 --> 00:09:37.868  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If you succeed in creating the overload,

182
00:09:37.952 --> 00:09:40.580  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
what makes you think you'll be
able to get out in time?

183
00:09:40.663 --> 00:09:44.166  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'll give everyone a chance
to get to the outer framework.

184
00:09:44.250 --> 00:09:46.669  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You'll be in charge of helping Hoshi.

185
00:09:46.752 --> 00:09:47.962  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And you, sir?

186
00:09:49.672 --> 00:09:52.049  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I have no plans of dying
on that weapon, Malcolm.

187
00:09:53.759 --> 00:09:55.803  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm gonna see
what else she's come up with.

188
00:10:03.477 --> 00:10:05.521  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
DANIELS:
This is a very important day, Jonathan.

189
00:10:05.605 --> 00:10:08.524  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I don't have time for this.
-It'll only take a minute.

190
00:10:08.608 --> 00:10:12.612  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You see the fellow in the blue jacket,
near the left end of the dais?

191
00:10:12.695 --> 00:10:15.823  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That's you,
a little more than seven years from now.

192
00:10:15.906 --> 00:10:18.034  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You and the others
are about to make history.

193
00:10:24.999 --> 00:10:27.752  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Do you remember I told you
about a federation?

194
00:10:28.502 --> 00:10:30.254  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What about it?

195
00:10:30.338 --> 00:10:31.922  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I work with some people
who are going to be

196
00:10:32.006 --> 00:10:33.591  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
pretty angry at me for telling you this,

197
00:10:33.674 --> 00:10:37.803  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but you're going to be an integral part
of forming that federation.

198
00:10:37.887 --> 00:10:39.805  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're down there right now,

199
00:10:39.889 --> 00:10:42.099  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
with Vulcans, Andorians, and Tellarites,

200
00:10:42.183 --> 00:10:44.143  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
getting ready to sign the charter.

201
00:10:44.226 --> 00:10:45.936  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The membership is going to grow...

202
00:10:46.020 --> 00:10:48.606  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
dozens, eventually hundreds of species.

203
00:10:48.689 --> 00:10:51.067  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A united federation of planets.

204
00:10:51.150 --> 00:10:53.736  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I have a team preparing
to board the weapon.

205
00:10:53.819 --> 00:10:55.529  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've got other things
to think about right now.

206
00:10:55.613 --> 00:10:58.115  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Let Reed or one of the others
go to the control platform.

207
00:10:58.199 --> 00:11:00.409  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What are you talking about?
-It's too great a risk.

208
00:11:00.493 --> 00:11:02.495  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If you're killed,
none of this will happen...

209
00:11:02.578 --> 00:11:04.205  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
At least,
not the way it's supposed to happen.

210
00:11:04.288 --> 00:11:06.540  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Then it'll happen some other way.

211
00:11:06.624 --> 00:11:09.251  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Who's to say whether
it'll be better or worse?

212
00:11:09.335 --> 00:11:12.004  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's essential you be a part of this.

213
00:11:13.130 --> 00:11:14.256  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Where are we?

214
00:11:14.340 --> 00:11:17.176  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What planet?
-Earth.

215
00:11:17.259 --> 00:11:20.763  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Seems to me it's just as essential
that Earth be around for this, too.

216
00:11:20.846 --> 00:11:22.723  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Lieutenant Reed can work with Sato.

217
00:11:22.807 --> 00:11:24.183  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( applause )

218
00:11:24.266 --> 00:11:26.811  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They are not crucial
to the future of mankind.

219
00:11:26.894 --> 00:11:28.145  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You are.

220
00:11:29.730 --> 00:11:34.527  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My mission is to save Earth,
not your federation.

221
00:11:34.610 --> 00:11:37.029  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You can't ignore your place in history.

222
00:11:40.116 --> 00:11:42.618  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My place is on that control platform.

223
00:11:42.701 --> 00:11:44.995  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now get me the hell back to Degra's ship.

224
00:11:47.665 --> 00:11:49.583  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And if it's not too much
of an inconvenience,

225
00:11:49.667 --> 00:11:55.423  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'd appreciate it if you'd contact
my first wife's third husband, Groznik.

226
00:11:57.383 --> 00:12:02.012  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Uh, tell him that he's welcome to keep
the Aldebaran drum set I loaned him.

227
00:12:02.096 --> 00:12:05.724  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, they have a child named Indaura.

228
00:12:06.517 --> 00:12:10.229  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Sweet little girl...
She must be, uh, 8 or 9 by now.

229
00:12:10.312 --> 00:12:11.939  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( laughs )

230
00:12:12.022 --> 00:12:16.694  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, I would like to leave her
my botanical library.

231
00:12:16.777 --> 00:12:18.821  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She always had a flair for plants.

232
00:12:18.904 --> 00:12:20.406  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Computer, pause recording.

233
00:12:22.533 --> 00:12:23.784  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Everything's ready here.

234
00:12:23.868 --> 00:12:25.161  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( clears throat )

235
00:12:25.244 --> 00:12:29.165  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Commander Tucker has completed
his modifications to the deflector.

236
00:12:30.416 --> 00:12:32.334  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I apologize if I interrupted you.

237
00:12:32.418 --> 00:12:34.587  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, no, no, don't be silly.

238
00:12:34.670 --> 00:12:38.466  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I was simply dictating a letter
to my colleague, Dr. Lucas.

239
00:12:38.549 --> 00:12:42.511  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He offered to make sure my affairs
were in order in the event that, uh...

240
00:12:43.679 --> 00:12:45.806  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, you know. ( chuckles )

241
00:12:46.765 --> 00:12:49.101  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've always found it distracting
to think of death,

242
00:12:49.185 --> 00:12:51.937  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
especially when entering
a dangerous situation.

243
00:12:52.021 --> 00:12:55.274  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Hmm. Hope for the best,
prepare for the worst.

244
00:12:55.357 --> 00:12:57.610  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't know about Vulcans,
but Denobulans take great pleasure

245
00:12:57.693 --> 00:13:00.696  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
in bequeathing their belongings
to far-flung relatives.

246
00:13:00.779 --> 00:13:01.989  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're not dead yet.

247
00:13:02.072 --> 00:13:04.283  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-( computer beeps )
-MAN: <i>Bridge to T'Pol.</i>

248
00:13:07.828 --> 00:13:08.954  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Go ahead.

249
00:13:09.038 --> 00:13:10.331  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>We're approaching the coordinates.</i>

250
00:13:10.414 --> 00:13:11.916  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Take us out of warp.

251
00:13:14.919 --> 00:13:16.420  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hope for the best, Doctor.

252
00:13:31.644 --> 00:13:33.896  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-( computer beeping )
-TRAVIS: It's grown.

253
00:13:33.979 --> 00:13:37.024  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's 100,000 kilometers deeper
than when we first detected it.

254
00:13:37.107 --> 00:13:39.818  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've enhanced the neuroleptic
compound as much as I can.

255
00:13:39.902 --> 00:13:41.529  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I strongly advise we remain

256
00:13:41.612 --> 00:13:44.573  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
in the disturbance
no longer than 15 minutes.

257
00:13:44.657 --> 00:13:46.617  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you ready to release the compound?

258
00:13:48.369 --> 00:13:49.620  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Then proceed.

259
00:13:49.703 --> 00:13:51.997  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Stand by to charge the deflector.

260
00:13:52.081 --> 00:13:53.707  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Set a course, Ensign.

261
00:13:56.293 --> 00:13:58.379  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
ARCHER: <i>Captain's starlog, supplemental.</i>

262
00:13:58.462 --> 00:14:01.215  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>We've begun to formulate a plan,</i>
<i>thanks to Hoshi,</i>

263
00:14:01.298 --> 00:14:04.927  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>who's made some progress</i>
<i>in decrypting the schematics.</i>

264
00:14:05.010 --> 00:14:07.221  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What have you guys figured out?

265
00:14:07.304 --> 00:14:10.015  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
ARCHER: We've got to disable
the reactor at a specific point

266
00:14:10.099 --> 00:14:12.017  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
during the inversion sequence,

267
00:14:12.101 --> 00:14:14.562  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but we don't know the sequence.

268
00:14:14.645 --> 00:14:16.564  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If it's not done in the right order,

269
00:14:16.647 --> 00:14:18.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
the internal safeguards will kick in,

270
00:14:18.524 --> 00:14:20.609  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and it'll be impossible
to create an overload.

271
00:14:20.693 --> 00:14:24.071  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I found the sequence,
but decrypting it is another story.

272
00:14:24.154 --> 00:14:27.116  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Your friend Degra didn't make this easy.

273
00:14:27.199 --> 00:14:29.451  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I wish I could tell you to take your time.

274
00:14:31.787 --> 00:14:34.039  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The first time you came
to visit me in Brazil...

275
00:14:34.123 --> 00:14:35.708  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It didn't stop raining for a week.

276
00:14:35.791 --> 00:14:37.835  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I had a bug then too.

277
00:14:37.918 --> 00:14:42.006  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
A tropical bacteria,
not a reptilian parasite.

278
00:14:44.300 --> 00:14:46.343  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I was sick as a dog,

279
00:14:46.427 --> 00:14:49.096  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but I wanted to make a good impression.

280
00:14:49.179 --> 00:14:50.931  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
When we get back home,

281
00:14:51.015 --> 00:14:56.020  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'll see to it you get some R&amp;R
in Norway or Canada...

282
00:14:56.103 --> 00:14:58.606  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
someplace where there's not
a tropical bug in sight.

283
00:14:58.689 --> 00:15:01.692  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Or reptiles.
-Or reptiles.

284
00:15:01.775 --> 00:15:03.819  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Keep at it.

285
00:15:03.903 --> 00:15:05.571  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll get these to the bridge.

286
00:15:10.951 --> 00:15:13.746  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We've gotten close enough
to isolate their signatures.

287
00:15:13.829 --> 00:15:17.666  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Insectoid ship is no longer with them.

288
00:15:17.750 --> 00:15:19.376  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why would they leave the vortex?

289
00:15:19.460 --> 00:15:20.878  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We have no idea.

290
00:15:20.961 --> 00:15:23.255  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
All we know is that the weapon
is being escorted

291
00:15:23.339 --> 00:15:26.467  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
by a single Reptilian vessel... Dolim's.

292
00:15:28.010 --> 00:15:30.763  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
At least we'll only have
one ship to contend with.

293
00:15:38.938 --> 00:15:40.147  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Here we go.

294
00:15:41.607 --> 00:15:44.109  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Doctor?
-Fifteen minutes and counting.

295
00:15:47.613 --> 00:15:49.657  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Any sign of the sphere?

296
00:15:49.740 --> 00:15:51.158  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's too soon.

297
00:15:52.993 --> 00:15:54.286  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hold your course.

298
00:15:57.456 --> 00:16:00.793  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Degra's vessel is less than
20 minutes behind us.

299
00:16:00.876 --> 00:16:03.712  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Lieutenant, we're about
to drop into normal space.

300
00:16:03.796 --> 00:16:06.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Stand by to initiate the firing sequence.</i>

301
00:16:06.924 --> 00:16:08.676  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're ready.

302
00:16:08.759 --> 00:16:11.303  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Are you detecting any Earth vessels
near the coordinates?

303
00:16:11.387 --> 00:16:15.140  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No vessels,
but there is one small orbital station.

304
00:16:17.768 --> 00:16:18.978  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Unarmed.

305
00:16:27.027 --> 00:16:28.654  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let me see Earth.

306
00:16:31.490 --> 00:16:33.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Enlarge.

307
00:16:39.540 --> 00:16:41.583  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's a shame.

308
00:16:41.667 --> 00:16:44.044  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
All that water.

309
00:16:44.128 --> 00:16:47.548  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Aquatics would feel at home here.

310
00:16:49.633 --> 00:16:51.010  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've got it.

311
00:16:51.093 --> 00:16:52.094  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How far?

312
00:16:52.177 --> 00:16:53.220  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
20,000 kilometers.

313
00:16:53.303 --> 00:16:54.722  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thirteen minutes left.

314
00:16:54.805 --> 00:16:57.266  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
As soon as we make visual contact,
go to thrusters.

315
00:16:57.349 --> 00:17:00.602  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Set a heading
to latitude 15 degrees north.

316
00:17:00.686 --> 00:17:03.022  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Deflector?
-Standing by.

317
00:17:13.741 --> 00:17:16.452  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're 800,000 kilometers ahead.

318
00:17:18.328 --> 00:17:19.455  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Get your team ready to go.

319
00:17:19.538 --> 00:17:21.165  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Aye, sir.

320
00:17:21.248 --> 00:17:23.792  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Dolim's changing course.

321
00:17:23.876 --> 00:17:26.170  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're heading for a space station.

322
00:17:26.253 --> 00:17:27.838  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are we in visual range?

323
00:17:32.301 --> 00:17:33.886  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yosemite Three?

324
00:17:33.969 --> 00:17:35.429  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A military installation?

325
00:17:35.512 --> 00:17:37.556  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A research post.

326
00:17:37.639 --> 00:17:40.100  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Usually 30 to 40 civilians aboard.

327
00:17:44.605 --> 00:17:47.566  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hail them on this frequency.

328
00:17:47.649 --> 00:17:48.984  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( computer beeps )

329
00:17:49.068 --> 00:17:50.986  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The weapon's emitting disruption waves.

330
00:17:51.070 --> 00:17:52.946  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I can't get anything through.

331
00:17:59.286 --> 00:18:00.829  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Fifteen degrees north.

332
00:18:00.913 --> 00:18:03.165  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Drop to 2,000 meters.

333
00:18:03.248 --> 00:18:06.210  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Track starboard, 82 mark zero.

334
00:18:06.293 --> 00:18:07.461  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Aye.

335
00:18:08.462 --> 00:18:10.964  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Doc, there's something weird
happening to my skin.

336
00:18:11.048 --> 00:18:12.758  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Me too!
-It was expected.

337
00:18:12.841 --> 00:18:15.177  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Try not to scratch it.
Eleven minutes remaining.

338
00:18:18.555 --> 00:18:21.517  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The guardians said
that once Earth is gone,

339
00:18:21.600 --> 00:18:24.937  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
we're to destroy all human colonies.

340
00:18:25.020 --> 00:18:28.565  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I see no reason not to begin
with this station.

341
00:18:28.649 --> 00:18:31.401  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Target. Fire when ready.

342
00:18:49.461 --> 00:18:51.130  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're heading back toward the weapon.

343
00:18:58.011 --> 00:18:59.638  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ten degrees port.

344
00:18:59.721 --> 00:19:01.765  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Slow to 30 kph.

345
00:19:01.849 --> 00:19:05.102  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm transferring the target point
to the deflector array.

346
00:19:07.020 --> 00:19:08.438  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Got it.

347
00:19:08.522 --> 00:19:09.940  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Begin.

348
00:19:15.904 --> 00:19:17.489  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Fish in a barrel.

349
00:19:20.159 --> 00:19:21.660  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Less than 10 minutes to go.

350
00:19:29.960 --> 00:19:32.212  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( indistinct conversations )

351
00:19:49.188 --> 00:19:51.190  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groans )

352
00:19:59.573 --> 00:20:00.908  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( rumbling )

353
00:20:00.991 --> 00:20:02.451  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What the hell's going on?

354
00:20:02.534 --> 00:20:04.036  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Power just fell 10%.

355
00:20:04.119 --> 00:20:06.830  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm picking up explosions on "E" deck.

356
00:20:06.914 --> 00:20:09.583  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Bridge to engineering. Report.

357
00:20:09.666 --> 00:20:11.543  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-( computer beeps )
-I'm losing the beam.

358
00:20:11.627 --> 00:20:13.629  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There are nine alien life-signs aboard.

359
00:20:13.712 --> 00:20:15.631  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They appear to be
trans-dimensional beings.

360
00:20:15.714 --> 00:20:17.841  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-How is that possible?
-This disturbance we're in,

361
00:20:17.925 --> 00:20:20.385  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
it's obviously been altered
enough to sustain them.

362
00:20:20.469 --> 00:20:23.347  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Who's on Degra's ship?

363
00:20:23.430 --> 00:20:28.268  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Eight primates, three Arboreals...
and seven humans.

364
00:20:29.353 --> 00:20:32.522  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Have their weapons been upgraded?
-No, sir.

365
00:20:32.606 --> 00:20:35.901  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Pathetic. Prepare to intercept.

366
00:20:38.362 --> 00:20:41.114  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're arming their torpedoes.

367
00:20:41.198 --> 00:20:42.324  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sir.

368
00:20:44.034 --> 00:20:46.703  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-How's Hoshi doing?
-She's holding up.

369
00:20:46.787 --> 00:20:49.164  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
She and the Macos
are at the transporter device.

370
00:20:51.458 --> 00:20:54.169  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Remember, no heroics.

371
00:20:54.253 --> 00:20:56.588  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Just get us in
and then keep them off your ass.

372
00:20:56.672 --> 00:20:59.424  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( computer beeping )

373
00:20:59.508 --> 00:21:02.010  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There's another vessel
approaching at high warp.

374
00:21:02.094 --> 00:21:03.345  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're asking for you.

375
00:21:06.974 --> 00:21:09.393  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>You're not using your head, pink-skin.</i>

376
00:21:09.476 --> 00:21:12.104  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>That ship you're on</i>
<i>is no match for the Reptilian.</i>

377
00:21:12.187 --> 00:21:14.273  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm busy, Shran. What are you doing here?

378
00:21:14.356 --> 00:21:17.943  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>You should be impressed we managed</i>
<i>to track you through the vortex.</i>

379
00:21:18.026 --> 00:21:21.196  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I anticipated that you'd need some help.</i>

380
00:21:29.746 --> 00:21:32.082  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( all groan )

381
00:21:32.165 --> 00:21:34.126  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
TUCKER: Corporal Kelly to the bridge.

382
00:21:34.209 --> 00:21:35.627  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Go ahead.

383
00:21:35.711 --> 00:21:37.629  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Our weapons are passing
right through them.

384
00:21:37.713 --> 00:21:40.132  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You got to stop this.
If I don't get full power back,

385
00:21:40.215 --> 00:21:42.175  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
this is gonna take three, four minutes
longer than we thought.

386
00:21:42.259 --> 00:21:43.635  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We can't afford three or four minutes.

387
00:21:43.719 --> 00:21:45.679  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Corporal Kelly, listen to me very closely.

388
00:21:45.762 --> 00:21:47.973  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Modulate your weapons
to a rotating frequency

389
00:21:48.056 --> 00:21:50.309  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
of 32.6 teracycles.

390
00:21:50.392 --> 00:21:52.311  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Doctor?
-Our trans-dimensional friend,

391
00:21:52.394 --> 00:21:53.812  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
the one we found in the pod...

392
00:21:53.895 --> 00:21:56.398  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I had quite a few hours
to study his physiology.

393
00:21:56.481 --> 00:21:59.318  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let's hope my memory serves me well.

394
00:21:59.401 --> 00:22:01.570  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll be right in front of you, gentlemen.

395
00:22:01.653 --> 00:22:03.947  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Keep a low profile.</i>

396
00:22:04.031 --> 00:22:05.782  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're matching speed.

397
00:22:05.866 --> 00:22:09.036  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You said there were
no human vessels in the vicinity.

398
00:22:09.119 --> 00:22:10.287  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're not human.

399
00:22:10.370 --> 00:22:13.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Destroy them both.

400
00:22:20.130 --> 00:22:23.258  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That third torpedo almost got you.
Be careful!

401
00:22:23.342 --> 00:22:24.676  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Prepare to come about to port.

402
00:22:24.760 --> 00:22:26.386  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Stay below me.</i>

403
00:22:26.470 --> 00:22:29.264  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We'll need to get
within a kilometer of the weapon.

404
00:22:29.347 --> 00:22:31.558  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Just stay below me.</i>

405
00:22:35.937 --> 00:22:38.690  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let's fight back this time, shall we?

406
00:22:38.774 --> 00:22:41.610  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Bring the forward cannons online.

407
00:22:52.746 --> 00:22:54.331  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
SHRAN: Go!

408
00:22:54.414 --> 00:22:57.751  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And tell Archer we're not even anymore.

409
00:22:57.834 --> 00:22:59.795  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He owes me!

410
00:23:10.972 --> 00:23:12.808  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( all groan )

411
00:23:24.945 --> 00:23:26.446  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's coming back.

412
00:23:26.530 --> 00:23:28.907  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Tell them to keep doing
what they're doing.

413
00:23:38.250 --> 00:23:40.001  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-( beep )
<i>-Walker to the bridge.</i>

414
00:23:40.085 --> 00:23:41.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Go ahead.
<i>-We've secured engineering,</i>

415
00:23:42.003 --> 00:23:43.922  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>but I don't think</i>
<i>we've seen the last of them.</i>

416
00:23:45.048 --> 00:23:47.008  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's time for you to work your magic,
Mr. Tucker.

417
00:23:47.092 --> 00:23:49.886  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Within five minutes, everyone in this ship
is going to start dying.

418
00:23:49.970 --> 00:23:51.263  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No pressure.

419
00:23:53.140 --> 00:23:56.268  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
OK, bring up the inversion sequence.

420
00:23:56.351 --> 00:23:59.604  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Start with the third one from the left.

421
00:24:11.324 --> 00:24:12.325  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Got it.

422
00:24:12.409 --> 00:24:14.035  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The second from the right.

423
00:24:25.881 --> 00:24:27.090  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( gasps )

424
00:24:27.174 --> 00:24:28.383  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hoshi?

425
00:24:30.385 --> 00:24:31.803  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm all right!

426
00:24:33.430 --> 00:24:36.391  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The first one on the left is next.

427
00:24:40.937 --> 00:24:44.482  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Commander, sensors show the humans
are no longer aboard Degra's vessel.

428
00:24:44.566 --> 00:24:47.694  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
These ships are drawing us away
from the weapon.

429
00:24:47.777 --> 00:24:49.321  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Get us back!

430
00:25:00.999 --> 00:25:02.250  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( rumbling )

431
00:25:02.334 --> 00:25:04.002  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-( computer beeps )
-What's going on?

432
00:25:04.085 --> 00:25:06.046  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Ignore it, Commander.
You've got less than two minutes.

433
00:25:10.884 --> 00:25:12.886  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Got it. Two to go.

434
00:25:17.891 --> 00:25:19.017  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groans )

435
00:25:20.602 --> 00:25:23.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( screaming )

436
00:25:45.043 --> 00:25:46.294  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groaning )

437
00:25:54.219 --> 00:25:55.303  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( gasps )

438
00:26:01.059 --> 00:26:02.310  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hoshi?

439
00:26:17.492 --> 00:26:19.327  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( grunting )

440
00:26:20.495 --> 00:26:21.496  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( communicator beeps )

441
00:26:21.579 --> 00:26:23.456  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Reed to Archer.
<i>-Go ahead.</i>

442
00:26:23.540 --> 00:26:25.250  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm pretty certain that was
the last of them, sir.

443
00:26:25.333 --> 00:26:27.419  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Good work. Now get back here.</i>

444
00:26:32.674 --> 00:26:35.051  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-( computer beeping )
-T'Pol.

445
00:26:35.135 --> 00:26:36.761  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-T'Pol!
-All right!

446
00:26:38.513 --> 00:26:41.308  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Take us to full impulse.
Get us out of here.

447
00:26:41.391 --> 00:26:42.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Wait a minute. I'm almost there!

448
00:26:42.684 --> 00:26:44.394  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You don't have a minute, Commander!

449
00:26:44.477 --> 00:26:46.563  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Then give me 10 seconds.
I'm telling you, I've got it.

450
00:26:52.527 --> 00:26:54.571  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-( computer beeping )
-That's it! Time's up!

451
00:26:54.654 --> 00:26:56.281  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It sure is.

452
00:27:05.165 --> 00:27:06.583  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now, Mr. Mayweather!

453
00:27:25.060 --> 00:27:26.811  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( choking )

454
00:27:32.400 --> 00:27:34.611  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( computer beeps )

455
00:27:34.694 --> 00:27:36.780  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The network is being destroyed.

456
00:27:36.863 --> 00:27:39.366  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Looks like we're getting out of this soup
faster than we thought.

457
00:27:39.449 --> 00:27:40.992  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Without the sphere,
their transformed space

458
00:27:41.076 --> 00:27:42.744  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
must be collapsing in on itself.

459
00:27:48.083 --> 00:27:49.501  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Which one, Hoshi?

460
00:27:49.584 --> 00:27:51.961  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Number four, the fourth one from the left.

461
00:27:52.045 --> 00:27:53.922  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Are you sure?
-Yes, yes.

462
00:27:54.005 --> 00:27:58.343  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Number five is the last one
after you disable the reactor.

463
00:28:05.475 --> 00:28:07.811  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But if we knock the reactor out,
won't that be enough?

464
00:28:07.894 --> 00:28:10.397  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We didn't come here
to disable this weapon.

465
00:28:11.564 --> 00:28:13.149  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're here to destroy it.

466
00:28:13.233 --> 00:28:14.442  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Give me the charges.

467
00:28:14.526 --> 00:28:16.111  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll take care of it, sir.

468
00:28:16.194 --> 00:28:18.988  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I want the four of you
to get to the outer framework.

469
00:28:19.072 --> 00:28:20.323  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Beam back to Degra's ship.

470
00:28:20.407 --> 00:28:21.825  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
As Chief Tactical Officer, sir--

471
00:28:21.908 --> 00:28:23.451  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This isn't open for debate, Lieutenant.

472
00:28:43.888 --> 00:28:45.515  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't worry, I'll be right behind you.

473
00:29:08.955 --> 00:29:10.206  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( beeping )

474
00:29:28.558 --> 00:29:30.518  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( alarm blaring )

475
00:29:35.774 --> 00:29:36.775  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ugh!

476
00:29:36.858 --> 00:29:39.986  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What have you done?

477
00:29:40.069 --> 00:29:41.237  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groans )

478
00:30:18.316 --> 00:30:21.820  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
One Reptilian transported to the weapon.

479
00:30:21.903 --> 00:30:24.948  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Let's make sure
he has nowhere to go back to.

480
00:30:25.031 --> 00:30:27.784  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They have no shielding
on their starboard engines.

481
00:30:27.867 --> 00:30:29.452  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Target all weapons.

482
00:30:36.376 --> 00:30:37.585  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Can you get a lock on him?

483
00:30:37.669 --> 00:30:38.962  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not yet.

484
00:30:39.045 --> 00:30:42.340  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Your captain is too deep
within the weapon.

485
00:31:01.109 --> 00:31:02.610  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groaning )

486
00:31:18.668 --> 00:31:20.044  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( beeping )

487
00:31:58.082 --> 00:32:02.503  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
T'POL: <i>Acting Captain's starlog,</i>
<i>February 14, 2152.</i>

488
00:32:02.587 --> 00:32:04.213  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>We're holding position at the coordinates</i>

489
00:32:04.297 --> 00:32:06.507  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>where we were told to meet</i>
<i>Degra's vessel.</i>

490
00:32:06.591 --> 00:32:09.177  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>So far, there's been no word from them.</i>

491
00:32:09.761 --> 00:32:14.390  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Long-range sensors are detecting
no evidence of the spheres.

492
00:32:14.474 --> 00:32:15.892  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
TUCKER: None of them?

493
00:32:15.975 --> 00:32:17.060  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
None.

494
00:32:20.355 --> 00:32:24.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And all the spatial anomalies
within our scanning range have vanished.

495
00:32:24.484 --> 00:32:27.070  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What about the thermobaric cloud barrier?

496
00:32:28.571 --> 00:32:31.824  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can only detect a small section
from our present location,

497
00:32:31.908 --> 00:32:35.453  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but it appears to be dissipating.

498
00:32:35.536 --> 00:32:37.538  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Looks like we kept our end of the bargain.

499
00:32:37.622 --> 00:32:41.376  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It would appear that the Expanse
is returning to normal space.

500
00:32:44.587 --> 00:32:46.714  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We should've heard something by now.

501
00:32:46.798 --> 00:32:48.091  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What if they failed?

502
00:32:48.800 --> 00:32:51.219  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Earth could be--

503
00:32:51.302 --> 00:32:52.679  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Be patient.

504
00:32:54.389 --> 00:32:56.224  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

505
00:32:57.308 --> 00:33:00.645  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And my skin's healing faster than yours.

506
00:33:01.312 --> 00:33:03.940  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I guess you Vulcans
aren't so tough after all.

507
00:33:04.023 --> 00:33:06.192  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Dr. Phlox says we should all
be back to normal

508
00:33:06.275 --> 00:33:07.568  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
within two to three days.

509
00:33:07.652 --> 00:33:09.404  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm only kidding.

510
00:33:11.531 --> 00:33:14.575  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You look nice like this,

511
00:33:14.659 --> 00:33:16.828  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
kind of like an old oil painting.

512
00:33:19.789 --> 00:33:21.916  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I am not old.

513
00:33:22.000 --> 00:33:25.253  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I will only be 66 years old
on my next birthday.

514
00:33:28.172 --> 00:33:30.591  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I can't believe you told me that.

515
00:33:30.675 --> 00:33:32.552  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You accused me of looking old.

516
00:33:32.635 --> 00:33:33.928  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's not what I mean.

517
00:33:34.012 --> 00:33:35.972  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've been trying to get you
to tell me your age

518
00:33:36.055 --> 00:33:37.765  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
since we left spacedock.

519
00:33:38.891 --> 00:33:40.518  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why now?

520
00:33:40.601 --> 00:33:45.314  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
To Vulcans, certain information
is considered intimate.

521
00:33:47.650 --> 00:33:49.777  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Intimate? Hmm...

522
00:33:49.861 --> 00:33:52.739  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-( computer beeps )
-TRAVIS: <i>Bridge to T'Pol.</i>

523
00:33:52.822 --> 00:33:54.365  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Go ahead.

524
00:33:54.449 --> 00:33:56.993  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>A vortex just opened. It's Degra's ship.</i>

525
00:33:58.995 --> 00:34:01.706  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( static )

526
00:34:02.790 --> 00:34:05.084  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is <i>Enterprise. </i>Please repeat.

527
00:34:08.337 --> 00:34:11.340  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Captain, did you stop the weapon?
-( static )

528
00:34:11.424 --> 00:34:13.051  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Captain?

529
00:34:13.134 --> 00:34:16.304  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( computer beeps )

530
00:34:16.387 --> 00:34:18.306  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Set an intercept course.

531
00:34:34.363 --> 00:34:36.449  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's done.

532
00:34:36.532 --> 00:34:37.825  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Done?

533
00:34:37.909 --> 00:34:40.995  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Captain Archer destroyed the weapon.

534
00:34:41.079 --> 00:34:42.789  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Where is he? Is he OK?

535
00:34:48.086 --> 00:34:50.004  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Captain didn't make it, Trip.

536
00:34:52.673 --> 00:34:54.550  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What do you mean, he didn't make it?

537
00:34:54.634 --> 00:34:59.305  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The weapon exploded
before he could transport to Degra's ship.

538
00:35:20.451 --> 00:35:22.578  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( computer beeps )

539
00:35:22.662 --> 00:35:24.122  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Come in.

540
00:35:28.668 --> 00:35:30.962  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thank you.

541
00:35:31.045 --> 00:35:34.882  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The Aquatic vessel should
have you home in less than a day.

542
00:35:36.926 --> 00:35:40.388  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I was pleased to hear that
the Council has agreed to reconvene.

543
00:35:40.471 --> 00:35:45.601  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It was difficult for the Insectoids
to ignore recent events.

544
00:35:45.685 --> 00:35:47.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And the Reptilians?

545
00:35:47.603 --> 00:35:50.022  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They will join us eventually.

546
00:35:50.106 --> 00:35:55.528  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They have no choice but to accept
that the guardians' promises were empty.

547
00:35:59.115 --> 00:36:02.952  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Your captain's sacrifice
will not be forgotten.

548
00:36:05.329 --> 00:36:06.998  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Safe journey.

549
00:36:09.125 --> 00:36:10.710  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thank you.

550
00:36:18.801 --> 00:36:21.012  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-( animals squeaking )
-It's all right.

551
00:36:21.095 --> 00:36:24.473  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's all right.
It won't be much longer, I promise.

552
00:36:24.557 --> 00:36:26.184  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

553
00:36:27.852 --> 00:36:29.312  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Is something wrong?

554
00:36:29.395 --> 00:36:32.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, I think they sense
that we are traveling

555
00:36:32.523 --> 00:36:34.192  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
in an unusual manner...

556
00:36:34.275 --> 00:36:37.653  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
In the, uh, belly of the beast,
so to speak.

557
00:36:37.737 --> 00:36:39.363  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There are no windows here.

558
00:36:39.447 --> 00:36:41.741  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
How would they know we're inside
the Aquatic vessel?

559
00:36:41.824 --> 00:36:43.868  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't have the slightest idea.

560
00:36:43.951 --> 00:36:46.495  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But I doubt I'll get much
peace and quiet around here

561
00:36:46.579 --> 00:36:48.623  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
until we are flying under our own power.

562
00:36:48.706 --> 00:36:50.499  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It'll only be a few more hours.

563
00:36:50.583 --> 00:36:51.918  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm...

564
00:36:52.418 --> 00:36:54.378  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Is there something I can do for you?

565
00:36:56.464 --> 00:36:58.674  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My skin hasn't fully healed yet.

566
00:37:01.093 --> 00:37:03.221  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, you're doing fine.

567
00:37:03.304 --> 00:37:08.309  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Vulcans are obviously more sensitive
to the effects of mysterious realms.

568
00:37:08.392 --> 00:37:10.853  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I guess we're not so tough after all.

569
00:37:11.395 --> 00:37:13.105  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Excuse me?

570
00:37:13.189 --> 00:37:15.358  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Is there anything I'll need to treat this?

571
00:37:16.859 --> 00:37:18.069  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Only time.

572
00:37:20.446 --> 00:37:21.697  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How's morale?

573
00:37:24.659 --> 00:37:27.203  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It isn't easy for a crew
to lose its captain.

574
00:37:29.330 --> 00:37:32.541  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I suppose we'll all need time to heal.

575
00:37:37.171 --> 00:37:38.673  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Will he be all right?

576
00:37:41.217 --> 00:37:42.718  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not for a while.

577
00:37:45.721 --> 00:37:47.473  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He lost his best friend.

578
00:37:49.517 --> 00:37:52.728  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But it's just a matter of time.

579
00:37:52.812 --> 00:37:54.522  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He'll be fine again.

580
00:37:55.940 --> 00:37:57.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Did you hear that?

581
00:37:58.234 --> 00:38:00.111  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The doctor says you'll be fine.

582
00:38:02.655 --> 00:38:04.490  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's just a matter of time.

583
00:38:20.131 --> 00:38:21.173  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
T'POL: Distance?

584
00:38:21.799 --> 00:38:23.926  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
800,000 kilometers.

585
00:38:24.385 --> 00:38:26.220  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Set a course, Ensign.

586
00:38:28.347 --> 00:38:29.890  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You should be in your quarters.

587
00:38:29.974 --> 00:38:31.684  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
With all due respect to Phlox,

588
00:38:31.767 --> 00:38:33.936  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I wouldn't miss this for the world.

589
00:38:38.691 --> 00:38:39.984  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mind if we take a look?

590
00:38:52.455 --> 00:38:55.458  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Prettiest sight I ever saw.

591
00:38:55.541 --> 00:38:57.335  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's all in one piece.

592
00:38:58.002 --> 00:38:59.670  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Captain would be proud.

593
00:39:00.921 --> 00:39:03.257  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Open a channel to Starfleet headquarters.

594
00:39:03.341 --> 00:39:04.633  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( computer beeping )

595
00:39:09.972 --> 00:39:11.515  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Strange.

596
00:39:11.599 --> 00:39:13.017  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What?

597
00:39:13.100 --> 00:39:14.852  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're not responding.

598
00:39:17.063 --> 00:39:19.690  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You'd think they'd be waiting
with bated breath.

599
00:39:19.774 --> 00:39:21.150  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Try another frequency.

600
00:39:23.110 --> 00:39:25.363  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not picking up the orbital platforms.

601
00:39:26.447 --> 00:39:29.325  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Reptilians destroyed Yosemite station.

602
00:39:29.408 --> 00:39:31.118  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's not just Yosemite.

603
00:39:31.952 --> 00:39:35.289  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's nothing coming from any of them.

604
00:39:35.956 --> 00:39:38.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've rotated through all the frequencies.

605
00:39:39.752 --> 00:39:42.046  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Contact the Lunar One colony.

606
00:39:42.129 --> 00:39:43.798  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I already tried.

607
00:39:48.135 --> 00:39:49.887  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Prepare a shuttlepod.

608
00:39:49.970 --> 00:39:52.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I want you and Ensign Mayweather
to get down to San Francisco.

609
00:39:52.723 --> 00:39:54.100  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Find out what's wrong.

610
00:40:11.992 --> 00:40:14.745  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Looks pretty normal to me.

611
00:40:15.246 --> 00:40:17.873  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Then why the hell doesn't anyone
want to talk to us?

612
00:40:18.707 --> 00:40:20.084  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

613
00:40:20.167 --> 00:40:23.587  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Land at the pad behind the command center.

614
00:40:23.671 --> 00:40:26.215  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Finally!
We've got three vessels approaching.

615
00:40:26.298 --> 00:40:27.675  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's about time.

616
00:40:27.758 --> 00:40:29.510  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( computer beeps )

617
00:40:29.593 --> 00:40:32.471  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This is Commander Charles Tucker
of the starship <i>Enterprise.</i>

618
00:40:32.555 --> 00:40:34.598  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You guys gave us quite a--
-( machine-gun fire )

619
00:40:36.100 --> 00:40:37.977  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What the hell?

620
00:40:38.769 --> 00:40:39.854  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sir.

621
00:40:53.617 --> 00:40:56.412  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( conversations in German )

